Package me.efekos.simpler.config

Class JSONDataManager<T extends Storable>

java.lang.Object
me.efekos.simpler.config.JSONDataManager<T>
Type Parameters:
T - Type of the data you want to store as a list. Be aware that using incompatible types in this type might cause errors. Just to let you know, there is a list of the classes compatible to be used inside T of database.
  • String.
  • Boolean.
  • Integer.
  • Double.
  • Long.
  • List<Object>.
  • null.
  • enum classes.
  • Any class that does not contain any type other than the ones above.
public class JSONDataManager<T extends Storable> extends Object
Deprecated.
Please use ListDataManager<T extends Storable>.
A basic database class made using Gson. You can store a List<T extends Storable> in this data. Use save() and load(Class) to load your data.

    • JSONDataManager

      public JSONDataManager(String path, org.bukkit.plugin.java.JavaPlugin plugin)
      Deprecated.
      Constructs a new manager.
      Parameters:
      path - Path to the file where all the data will be saved with save(). Must end with .json. You can't choose a path outside your plugins data folder.
      plugin - Instance of the plugin that will use this database. Recommended to be this, assuming that you are constructing a database inside your JavaPlugin.onEnable() method.
